WEBVTT

00:02.711 --> 00:04.129
{\an8}Boy: IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL
FULL OF BULLIES,

00:04.212 --> 00:05.588
{\an8}INSANE TEACHERS,

00:05.672 --> 00:08.258
{\an8}AND GROSS SCHOOL LUNCHES,

00:08.341 --> 00:10.885
{\an8}NED BIGBY--THAT'S ME--
AND MY TWO BEST FRIENDS

00:10.969 --> 00:12.345
{\an8}TRY TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE:

00:12.429 --> 00:13.596
CREATE A GUIDE THAT WILL
HELP YOU SURVIVE SCHOOL.

00:13.680 --> 00:17.058
{\an8}Man: ♪ TURN IT UP ♪

00:17.142 --> 00:18.768
{\an8}♪ LOOKING OUT ♪

00:18.852 --> 00:21.521
{\an8}♪ I'LL SURVIVE WITH NO DOUBT ♪

00:21.604 --> 00:23.231
{\an8}♪ NEVER FEAR ♪

00:23.314 --> 00:24.983
{\an8}♪ BRING IT ON ♪

00:25.066 --> 00:27.444
{\an7}♪ BREAKING DOWN
WHAT'S IN MY WAY ♪

00:27.527 --> 00:32.448
{\an8}♪ AND I'M ♪

00:32.531 --> 00:34.659
{\an7}♪ FINDING MY PLACE
IN THIS WORLD ♪

00:34.743 --> 00:36.619
{\an8}♪ AND I... ♪

00:36.703 --> 00:39.080
{\an8}Boy: "NED'S DECLASSIFIED
SCHOOL SURVIVAL GUIDE."

00:39.164 --> 00:41.124
{\an8}YOUR RESULTS MAY VARY.

00:41.207 --> 00:43.251
{\an8}CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION
AND NICKELODEON

00:43.334 --> 00:45.962
{\an1}SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO TELL
YOUR FRIEND SOMETHING

00:46.045 --> 00:48.381
AND IT CANNOT WAIT
TILL AFTER CLASS,

00:48.465 --> 00:49.632
SO YOU PASS THEM A NOTE.

00:49.716 --> 00:53.344
NED, PASS THIS NOTE
TO SUZIE.

00:53.428 --> 00:56.639
{\an4}HERE ARE SOME TIPS ON
THE BEST WAY TO PASS A NOTE
AND NOT GET CAUGHT.

00:59.184 --> 01:00.810
DON'T PHYSICALLY PASS THE NOTE.

01:00.894 --> 01:03.313
USE A FOOT NOTE INSTEAD.

01:11.404 --> 01:14.073
IF YOU GO PAPERLESS
AND TEXT MESSAGE YOUR NOTE,

01:14.157 --> 01:17.160
{\an8}MAKE SURE YOUR RINGER
IS TURNED OFF.

01:17.243 --> 01:18.620
{\an8}[CELL PHONE RINGS]

01:18.703 --> 01:20.413
NOW, I'M NOT TELLING YOU
TO PASS NOTES,

01:20.497 --> 01:21.706
BUT IF YOU DO, BE CAREFUL.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.166
PASS THIS TO SUZIE.

01:25.710 --> 01:28.046
HAND IT OVER, MR. BIGBY.

01:28.922 --> 01:32.967
NO NOTES IN MY CLASS,
MR. BIGBY!

01:33.051 --> 01:37.972
{\an5}NOW YOU OWE ME
A 1,000-WORD PAPER
ON CELL DIVISION.

01:38.056 --> 01:39.015
BUT I DIDN'T WRITE IT.

01:39.098 --> 01:41.518
WELL, THEN, WHO DID?

02:01.913 --> 02:03.039
THANKS A LOT.

02:03.122 --> 02:04.833
{\an4}NOW I HAVE TO WRITE
A 1,000-WORD REPORT
ON CELL DIVISION.

02:04.916 --> 02:07.043
AND WHOSE FAULT IS THAT?

02:07.126 --> 02:08.669
NEXT TIME,
DON'T GET CAUGHT.

02:11.047 --> 02:13.550
{\an5}I GOT A LOVE NOTE!

02:11.047 --> 02:13.550
I NEED A LATE NOTE.

02:13.633 --> 02:15.552
YOU GO FIRST.

02:15.635 --> 02:17.178
{\an1}SOMEONE WROTE ME
A SECRET LOVE NOTE.

02:17.262 --> 02:19.472
{\an1}IT'S A LITTLE SAPPY,
BUT IT'S REALLY NICE, TOO.

02:19.556 --> 02:21.349
AND IT'S WRITTEN
IN CALLIGRAPHY.

02:21.432 --> 02:23.685
YEAH, ON SECOND THOUGHT,
YOU GO FIRST.

02:23.768 --> 02:26.437
{\an5}I WAS LATE FOR GYM,
AND NOW DIRGA
WANTS A NOTE.

02:26.521 --> 02:27.397
WHY WERE YOU LATE?

02:28.815 --> 02:31.693
YEAH! OH, YEAH!
WHOO!

02:31.776 --> 02:33.319
HA HA HA!

02:47.292 --> 02:49.878
MOP BUCKET CHICKEN.

02:49.961 --> 02:51.421
IF I DON'T GET DIRGA
A NOTE FROM A TEACHER

02:51.504 --> 02:52.213
EXPLAINING WHY
I WAS LATE,

02:52.297 --> 02:53.756
I'LL OWE HER
1,000 PUSH-UPS.

02:53.840 --> 02:54.924
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO?

02:55.008 --> 02:56.676
HAVE YOU HEARD OF
LE FORGER?

02:56.759 --> 02:58.469
LE FORGER? WHO'S THAT?

02:58.553 --> 03:02.932
HE'S A MYSTERIOUS FIGURE WHO IS
THE BEST NOTE FORGER IN SCHOOL.

03:03.016 --> 03:04.350
NOBODY KNOWS HIS TRUE IDENTITY.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.602
HOW DO I MEET HIM?

03:05.685 --> 03:08.104
GET A BOX OF
COCONUT MACAROONS.

03:08.187 --> 03:09.939
THAT'S HOW HE LIKES
TO BE PAID.

03:10.023 --> 03:12.817
{\an5}GO TO THE LUNCHROOM
BULLETIN BOARD
AND LEAVE A NOTE.

03:12.901 --> 03:14.027
THEN HE'LL
CONTACT YOU.

03:23.536 --> 03:26.247
{\an1}HEY, NED, COULD YOU PASS
THIS NOTE TO YOURSELF?

03:27.582 --> 03:31.252
[GIRLS LAUGH]

03:33.212 --> 03:34.547
{\an4}I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
GOING TO TAKE THE RAP
FOR BITSY

03:34.631 --> 03:35.506
AND WRITE THAT REPORT.

03:35.590 --> 03:37.342
I HAVE TO WRITE
THE REPORT.

03:37.425 --> 03:38.801
{\an5}WHAT ELSE AM I
GOING TO DO?
BE A RAT?

03:38.885 --> 03:41.095
I GOT ANOTHER LOVE NOTE.

03:42.555 --> 03:45.183
SOMEBODY WROTE YOU
A LOVE NOTE?

03:45.266 --> 03:46.351
{\an1}YEAH.
I FOUND IT TODAY AND--

03:47.852 --> 03:50.063
WHY AM I TELLING YOU?

03:50.146 --> 03:52.231
{\an1}YOU WOULD
NEVER UNDERSTAND.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.983
ANYWAY, I THINK
SETH WROTE THEM.

03:54.067 --> 03:59.197
ORANGE...
ORANGE...ORANGE!

03:59.280 --> 04:02.825
{\an8}YEAH, HE'S CLEARLY
A DEEP THINKER.

04:02.909 --> 04:05.078
HE'S CLEARLY A HOTTIE,

04:05.161 --> 04:06.454
{\an1}AND HE'S IN
MY HISTORY CLASS,

04:06.537 --> 04:08.331
{\an1}WHICH IS WHERE I FOUND
THE FIRST NOTE.

04:08.414 --> 04:09.540
IT'S GOT TO BE SETH.

04:11.668 --> 04:13.127
{\an5}[BELL RINGS]

04:11.668 --> 04:13.127
OK, YOUNG PEOPLE.

04:13.211 --> 04:15.171
PLEASE PUT YOUR PROJECTS
ON THE TABLE IN THE BACK.

04:15.254 --> 04:17.673
{\an1}I'LL GET TO THEM
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

04:18.882 --> 04:22.512
OK. NEEDS TO BE SUBTLE.

04:22.595 --> 04:24.013
{\an1}WORK THE LOVE NOTE
INTO THE CONVERSATION

04:24.097 --> 04:26.808
{\an1}AND GET HIM TO ADMIT
HE WROTE IT.

04:26.891 --> 04:28.309
{\an1}DID YOU WRITE
THIS LOVE NOTE?

04:28.393 --> 04:32.355
NO. THIS IS SO SAPPY.

04:32.438 --> 04:33.356
I WRITE POEMS.

04:33.439 --> 04:35.316
DO YOU WANT TO HEAR ONE?

04:35.400 --> 04:40.196
ROSES ARE RED,
BASKETBALLS ARE ORANGE.

04:40.279 --> 04:41.281
I'M KIND OF STUCK
AFTER THAT.

04:41.364 --> 04:44.951
DO YOU KNOW A WORD
THAT RHYMES WITH ORANGE?

04:57.296 --> 04:59.882
CHANDRA, DO YOU KNOW
WHOSE PROJECT THIS IS?

04:59.966 --> 05:02.093
I THINK IT'S LOOMER'S.

05:02.176 --> 05:04.178
LOOMER'S?!

05:21.988 --> 05:23.448
Le Forger: ENTER.

05:35.668 --> 05:36.586
I NEED A NOTE.

05:36.669 --> 05:37.879
Le Forger: SHH!

05:37.962 --> 05:39.338
THE COCONUT MACAROONS?

05:48.806 --> 05:52.310
MMM.

05:52.393 --> 05:54.145
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

05:57.982 --> 06:00.526
{\an5}OK, COOK.
NOTE ACCEPTED,
SO NO PUSH-UPS.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.742
{\an4}HEY.
HOW'S THE 1,000-WORD
REPORT COMING?

06:07.825 --> 06:09.410
ONLY 1,000 WORDS TO GO.

06:09.494 --> 06:12.955
{\an5}HOW'S YOUR SUPERSAPPY
SECRET LOVE NOTE WRITER
SEARCH GOING?

06:13.039 --> 06:15.208
{\an1}I THINK IT WAS
WRITTEN BY LOOMER.

06:15.291 --> 06:16.334
EXCUSE ME.

06:19.087 --> 06:20.588
LOOMER?!

06:20.671 --> 06:23.257
{\an4}DO YOU THINK
THERE'S A ROMANTIC
DEEP INSIDE LOOMER?

06:27.095 --> 06:29.097
NO, BUT THERE'S DAISIES.

06:33.226 --> 06:34.519
LE FORGER'S NOTE WORKED!

06:34.602 --> 06:37.563
AND FOR ONLY 20 BOXES OF
COCONUT MACAROONS,

06:37.647 --> 06:39.065
{\an1}HE'LL GIVE ME HIS
PERSONAL PAGER NUMBER.

06:39.148 --> 06:41.776
I'LL HAVE ACCESS 24/7.

06:41.859 --> 06:45.947
{\an1}I CAN DO ANYTHING I WANT,
AND NO ONE CAN STOP ME.

06:46.030 --> 06:49.659
YEAH, I'M SURE
THAT'LL GO WELL.

06:49.742 --> 06:50.827
THIS IS KILLING ME.

06:50.910 --> 06:52.328
I NEED TO GET A SAMPLE
OF LOOMER'S HANDWRITING

06:52.411 --> 06:54.247
{\an1}AND FIND OUT IF
HE WROTE THESE LOVE NOTES.

06:54.330 --> 06:56.833
YEAH, I SHOULD GET BACK
TO WORK ON MY PROJECT.

06:56.916 --> 06:58.876
DID I MENTION IT HAS
TO BE 1,000 WORDS?

07:03.923 --> 07:05.675
♪ 1, 2, 3, 4 ♪

07:10.096 --> 07:11.097
[BEEPING]

07:11.180 --> 07:14.100
{\an1}♪ TOO MUCH OF A GOOD THING
CAN BE A GREAT THING ♪

07:14.183 --> 07:17.019
♪ DON'T TRY TO STOP ME NOW ♪

07:17.103 --> 07:21.232
♪ WHOO-HOO, WHOO-HOO ♪

07:24.610 --> 07:26.028
♪ TOO MUCH OF THE BEST ♪

07:29.615 --> 07:34.996
♪ SO CAN YOU FEEL ME NOW? ♪

08:03.274 --> 08:04.525
♪ WHOO-HOO ♪

08:17.663 --> 08:21.459
{\an1}♪ TOO MUCH OF A GOOD THING
CAN BE A GREAT THING ♪

08:21.542 --> 08:22.710
♪ DON'T TRY TO STOP ME NOW ♪

08:42.730 --> 08:44.565
NO!

08:47.693 --> 08:49.612
A 1,000-WORD REPORT.

08:49.695 --> 08:52.198
I DON'T EVEN KNOW 1,000 WORDS.

08:52.281 --> 08:53.241
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

08:53.324 --> 08:56.535
I OWE A 5-PAGE REPORT ON
THE PYTHAGOREAN THEOREM.

08:56.619 --> 08:56.953
I CAN'T STAND BITSY.

08:57.036 --> 08:59.288
LET ME GUESS.

08:59.372 --> 09:00.331
SHE ASKED YOU TO PASS A NOTE,

09:00.414 --> 09:02.625
AND YOU GOT NABBED.

09:02.708 --> 09:03.918
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED TO ME.

09:04.001 --> 09:05.878
Kids: ME, TOO!

09:08.839 --> 09:12.301
{\an4}I SAY WE GIVE
BITSY A TASTE OF
HER OWN MEDICINE.

09:12.385 --> 09:13.469
YEAH!

09:13.552 --> 09:15.638
{\an1}I SAY WE COME UP WITH
A DIABOLICAL PLAN

09:15.721 --> 09:15.972
TO GET BITSY IN TROUBLE.

09:16.055 --> 09:17.306
YEAH!

09:17.390 --> 09:19.308
{\an1}I SAY WE FINISH
OUR PROJECTS FIRST

09:19.392 --> 09:20.643
SO WE DON'T GET
IN MORE TROUBLE.

09:20.726 --> 09:28.401
YEAH.

09:28.401 --> 09:29.318
[SIGHS]

09:29.402 --> 09:31.487
THIS IS IT.
I'M GOING IN.

09:31.570 --> 09:33.030
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M DOING THIS.

09:35.408 --> 09:36.033
I KNOW YOU WROTE THESE.

09:36.117 --> 09:39.495
DID YOU LIKE THEM?

09:39.578 --> 09:42.540
ACTUALLY, YEAH.

09:42.623 --> 09:43.958
I DON'T GET IT.

09:44.041 --> 09:46.168
{\an5}YOU BEAT PEOPLE UP
AND THEN YOU WRITE
BEAUTIFUL LOVE NOTES?

09:46.252 --> 09:48.004
I'M A COMPLEX INDIVIDUAL.

09:48.087 --> 09:50.214
WHAT ARE THESE?

09:50.298 --> 09:52.800
{\an1}OOH, SAPPY LOVE NOTES.
WHO WROTE THESE?

09:54.093 --> 09:56.762
[GASPS]

09:56.846 --> 09:59.515
I DON'T WRITE LOVE NOTES.

09:59.598 --> 10:01.434
I EAT THEM.

10:01.517 --> 10:03.728
{\an1}[MUFFLED] SHE'S JUST
KIDDING AROUND.

10:04.186 --> 10:06.731
RIGHT, JENNIFER?

10:08.941 --> 10:10.484
{\an1}TELL THEM YOU'RE
JUST KIDDING AROUND.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.321
RIGHT, I'M JUST
KIDDING AROUND.

10:13.404 --> 10:16.073
{\an1}OH, MAN!

10:16.157 --> 10:20.536
{\an5}MAN, WE WERE SCARED
FOR A SECOND.
HA HA!

10:26.334 --> 10:28.711
WE KNEW THESE NOTES
WERE FORGED, COOK.

10:28.794 --> 10:31.005
{\an5}WE'VE BEEN TRYING
TO NAB LE FORGER
ALL YEAR,

10:31.088 --> 10:32.673
SO WE FOLLOWED YOU.

10:32.757 --> 10:35.217
{\an1}YOUR NOTE PASSING DAYS
ARE OVER!

10:35.301 --> 10:38.054
{\an1}AND NOW YOU'VE LED US
RIGHT TO LE FORGER'S LAIR.

10:38.137 --> 10:40.890
[TEACHERS LAUGH]

10:55.404 --> 10:57.531
[LAUGHTER STOPS]

10:57.615 --> 10:59.992
[OWL HOOTS]

11:03.746 --> 11:05.748
YOUR PAPER, MR. BIGBY?

11:14.173 --> 11:17.510
{\an1}BITSY, COULD YOU PASS
THIS NOTE TO COCONUT HEAD?

11:18.969 --> 11:19.804
BITSY, COULD YOU PASS
THIS NOTE ALONG?

11:22.348 --> 11:23.349
UH, I...

11:39.990 --> 11:42.952
UH, I...I...I...I MEAN...

11:43.035 --> 11:43.828
BUT I...BUT...

11:46.247 --> 11:48.332
BITSY GOT BUSTED WITH
SO MANY NOTES,

11:48.416 --> 11:52.461
{\an4}SHE HAS TO WRITE SWEENEY
A 10,000-WORD REPORT
ON CHLOROPHYLL.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.296
{\an5}LOOMER WROTE ME
A LOVE NOTE,
AND THEN HE ATE IT.

11:54.380 --> 11:58.884
{\an4}AND I HAVE TO GET A NOTE
EXPLAINING EVERYTHING I DID
SIGNED BY MY MOTHER.

11:58.968 --> 11:59.593
I'M DEAD MEAT.

11:59.677 --> 12:01.887
{\an1}AT LEAST LE FORGER
GOT AWAY.

12:09.395 --> 12:10.688
MMM.

12:15.234 --> 12:17.194
Ned: BEST FRIENDS.

12:17.278 --> 12:19.738
THEY KEEP EACH OTHER'S SECRETS,

12:19.822 --> 12:23.117
UNDERSTAND EACH OTHER'S
PROBLEMS,

12:23.200 --> 12:25.911
{\an1}AND SOMETIMES HACK INTO
THE SCHOOL'S SERVER

12:25.995 --> 12:27.079
AND CHANGE THE LUNCH MENU

12:27.163 --> 12:28.831
BECAUSE YOU HATE
BRUSSELS SPROUTS.

12:30.750 --> 12:35.004
{\an5}DONE.
TODAY'S VEGETABLE:
CANDY CORN.

12:35.087 --> 12:37.006
NOW FOR
TOMORROW'S...

12:37.089 --> 12:39.675
{\an7}Ned: AND BEST FRIENDS ALWAYS
LOOK OUT FOR EACH OTHER,

12:39.758 --> 12:41.469
{\an7}EVEN THOUGH SOMETIMES
THEY DO BUTT HEADS.

12:42.219 --> 12:44.889
HELMETS!

12:46.891 --> 12:50.978
{\an1}GOOD MORNING, LOSERS.
HA HA HA!

12:53.689 --> 12:55.983
AND BEST FRIENDS
ALWAYS STAND TOGETHER.

12:56.066 --> 12:59.987
HEY, HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO BE A KILLER B-E-E?

13:00.070 --> 13:05.367
{\an1}AND GET THIS SUPERCOOL
K. B. J-A-C-K-E-T?

13:05.451 --> 13:06.702
{\an1}YOU WANT COOKIE AND ME
TO BE KILLER BEES?

13:06.785 --> 13:08.621
JUST COOKIE,
NOT YOU.

13:23.886 --> 13:25.221
YOU ARE SO C-O-O-L.

13:25.304 --> 13:27.473
King Bee: YEAH!

13:29.850 --> 13:32.394
YEARBOOK SURVEY.
PASS THEM BACK.

13:32.478 --> 13:33.896
{\an5}YEARBOOK SURVEY.
PASS THEM BACK.

13:33.979 --> 13:35.856
YEARBOOK SURVEY.
PASS THEM BACK.

13:39.318 --> 13:41.237
{\an5}YEARBOOK SURVEY.
PASS THEM BACK.

13:41.320 --> 13:43.656
1: YOU'RE NOT ON
THE YEARBOOK,

13:43.739 --> 13:45.658
AND 2: WHAT ARE YOU
UP TO?

13:45.741 --> 13:47.243
{\an1}YOU KNOW HOW
YOU AND COOKIE

13:47.326 --> 13:48.369
{\an1}ALWAYS COME UP
WITH THESE PLANS

13:48.452 --> 13:49.161
{\an1}THAT I SAY
ARE REALLY CRAZY,

13:49.245 --> 13:50.579
{\an1}BUT THEN THEY WORK OUT
IN THE END?

13:50.663 --> 13:52.706
I'M FAMILIAR
WITH THE PROCESS.

13:52.790 --> 13:55.000
"DO YOU LIKE VOLLEYBALL?
YES OR NO?

13:55.084 --> 13:57.461
{\an5}IS MATH YOUR
FAVORITE SUBJECT?
YES OR NO?"

13:57.545 --> 13:59.922
THIS IS JUST A YES OR NO
QUIZ ON THINGS YOU LIKE.

14:00.005 --> 14:01.757
YES, I KNOW.

14:01.840 --> 14:03.676
{\an1}I PASS IT OUT, AND THE GIRL
WHO SCORES THE HIGHEST

14:03.759 --> 14:05.177
{\an1}BECOMES MY NEW
BEST FRIEND.

14:05.261 --> 14:05.553
IT'S CRAZY, RIGHT?

14:05.636 --> 14:07.513
OH, YEAH.

14:07.596 --> 14:10.224
{\an4}BUT NOT AS CRAZY AS
THE WHOLE COOKIE/
KILLER BEE THING.

14:10.307 --> 14:11.600
{\an5}...E-E.

14:10.307 --> 14:11.600
[LAUGHTER]

14:11.684 --> 14:12.935
YOU'RE THE DUDE, MAN!

14:13.018 --> 14:15.396
THEY'RE UP TO SOMETHING.

14:15.479 --> 14:16.480
DON'T SWEAT IT.

14:16.564 --> 14:17.731
COOKIE IS NOT DUMB ENOUGH

14:17.815 --> 14:20.442
{\an1}TO GET MIXED UP WITH
THOSE MEAN SPELLING JERKS.

14:27.449 --> 14:30.953
YO, NED, WHAT DO YOU
T-H-I-N-K?

14:31.036 --> 14:33.455
{\an1}I THINK THE KILLER BEES
ARE EVIL.

14:33.539 --> 14:36.959
{\an5}I THOUGHT SO, TOO,
UNTIL THEY STARTED BEING
REALLY NICE TO ME.

14:37.042 --> 14:39.086
WHY WOULD THE KILLER BEES
WANT YOU TO BE WITH THEM?

14:39.169 --> 14:40.087
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

14:40.170 --> 14:41.088
WHAT, YOU DON'T THINK

14:41.171 --> 14:43.424
{\an5}I'M TOUGH, COOL,
OR SMART ENOUGH
TO BE A BEE?

14:43.507 --> 14:46.093
NO, NO, YOU'RE...SMART.

14:46.176 --> 14:48.304
BUT NOT COOL
OR TOUGH ENOUGH.

14:48.387 --> 14:49.722
SO I'M JUST SOME
BIG OLD DIGITAL FREAK

14:49.805 --> 14:53.601
NOT WORTHY OF
THE K. B. J-A-C-K-E-T.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.144
DON'T SPELL AT ME.

14:55.227 --> 14:56.812
{\an1}ALL I'M SAYING IS
THEY'RE UP TO SOMETHING.

14:56.895 --> 14:59.148
NED'S JUST JEALOUS
HE WASN'T ASKED TO JOIN,

14:59.231 --> 15:01.817
AND NOW HE'S
L-O-N-E-L-Y.

15:01.900 --> 15:05.362
I AM NOT...LONELY.

15:05.446 --> 15:09.366
IN FACT, I'M HANGING WITH
THE COOLEST GUY IN SCHOOL.

15:09.450 --> 15:12.036
SETH! SHOOTING HOOPS LATER?

15:12.119 --> 15:14.330
ALL RIGHT,
YOU'RE THE BEST, DUDE!

15:14.413 --> 15:16.040
LATER.

15:16.123 --> 15:19.209
{\an5}AW, YEAH, MAN!
YOU'RE THE COOLEST!
HA HA!

15:26.634 --> 15:30.012
{\an4}DO YOURSELF A FAVOR
AND SKIP THE CHOPPED
CHUCK ON MASH.

15:30.095 --> 15:39.813
WHY?

15:39.813 --> 15:41.315
TRY THE CANDY CORN.

15:43.984 --> 15:46.612
{\an5}SO, HOW'S YOUR CRAZY
FIND-A-BEST-GIRLFRIEND
PLAN GOING?

15:46.695 --> 15:49.782
GRADING THEM AS WE SPEAK.

15:49.865 --> 15:50.449
{\an1}BOY. BOY.

15:50.532 --> 15:52.368
EWW, CRABGRASS.

15:52.451 --> 15:54.536
[KILLER BEES LAUGHING]

15:59.625 --> 16:01.877
DON'T WORRY ABOUT COOKIE.

16:01.960 --> 16:03.045
HE JUST WANTS THE JACKET.

16:03.128 --> 16:03.712
I'M NOT WORRIED.

16:03.796 --> 16:04.713
{\an1}EVEN IF YOU HATE
THE BEES,

16:04.797 --> 16:06.840
YOU GOT TO LOVE
THOSE JACKETS.

16:06.924 --> 16:07.716
AAH!

16:07.800 --> 16:10.678
{\an1}SOMEBODY JUST
SCORED 100 ON MY SURVEY!

16:10.761 --> 16:11.679
AAH!

16:11.762 --> 16:13.597
AAH!

16:13.681 --> 16:15.391
DORIS TREMBLY?

16:21.480 --> 16:22.314
OH, YOU'RE NOT GOING
OVER THERE, ARE YOU?

16:22.398 --> 16:24.650
{\an1}I HAVE TO.

16:24.733 --> 16:25.442
SHE SCORED 100.

16:25.526 --> 16:28.904
ALL RIGHT.
I'M HERE IF YOU NEED ME.

16:28.987 --> 16:29.071
BUT PLEASE
DON'T NEED ME.

16:40.165 --> 16:42.668
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

16:42.751 --> 16:44.169
I SWEAR I FOUND IT!

16:44.253 --> 16:46.046
{\an1}YOU CAN'T PROVE A THING!
IT WAS HER!

16:46.130 --> 16:48.424
NO, I JUST WANTED
TO SAY HI,

16:48.507 --> 16:50.634
AND MAYBE SOMETIME
WE COULD TALK.

16:52.094 --> 16:55.431
{\an1}WHAT'S NED LIKE?
WILL HE GO OUT WITH ME?

16:55.514 --> 16:57.558
[GIRLS TALK SIMULTANEOUSLY]

16:57.641 --> 17:00.477
YOU ARE THE M-A-N!

17:00.561 --> 17:02.730
Queen Bee: YOU ARE SO C-O-O-L.

17:02.813 --> 17:04.481
AH, THAT WAS SWEET!

17:04.565 --> 17:07.108
{\an1}AND SOON YOU WILL BE
A B-E-E.

17:07.192 --> 17:08.234
Killer Bees: OH!

17:08.318 --> 17:10.612
HEY, LOSERS!

17:10.695 --> 17:13.449
{\an1}WHERE'S THE OTHER
LOSER HEAD?

17:13.531 --> 17:15.075
[LAUGHTER]

17:15.159 --> 17:18.537
{\an1}HE'S A BEE?
I HATE THE BEES!

17:18.619 --> 17:19.079
NICE JACKETS, THOUGH.

17:25.461 --> 17:27.628
ORANGE...

17:27.713 --> 17:29.089
HA HA HA HA!

17:29.173 --> 17:31.550
THAT'S HILARIOUS,
SETH!

17:31.633 --> 17:33.719
OH, AND I'LL SEE YOU
AT MY PARTY TONIGHT.

17:33.802 --> 17:35.971
HA HA!
YOU'RE HILARIOUS!

17:36.054 --> 17:36.847
HA HA HA HA HA!

17:36.930 --> 17:39.641
MAN, IT'S GREAT
TO BE BUDDIES.

17:39.725 --> 17:40.100
{\an1}HA HA.
GOTTA GO. BYE.

17:43.562 --> 17:46.482
FORGET NED.

17:46.565 --> 17:49.318
YOU'RE A BEE NOW.

17:49.401 --> 17:49.943
WHEN DO I GET
THE JACKET?

17:50.027 --> 17:52.237
{\an5}SOON.
S-O-O-N.
SOON.

17:58.410 --> 18:00.662
NOW AS AN OFFICIAL
MEMBER OF THE CREW,

18:00.746 --> 18:02.998
TELL US MORE ABOUT NED!

18:03.081 --> 18:03.999
DOES HE LIKE TO SWIM?

18:04.082 --> 18:05.876
[GIRLS TALK SIMULTANEOUSLY]

18:05.959 --> 18:12.758
{\an1}OR, OR, OR...COULD WE
DO SOMETHING ELSE?

18:12.841 --> 18:19.181
WELL...WE COULD
REARRANGE YOUR FACE.

18:25.437 --> 18:26.855
BABY INSPECTION!

18:26.939 --> 18:29.650
REMEMBER, THIS WEEK'S ASSIGNMENT
WAS TREATING DIAPER RASH.

18:29.733 --> 18:32.694
{\an1}YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO WASH
AND POWDER YOUR BABY.

18:33.821 --> 18:37.032
OH, TELL ME
YOU WASHED THE BABY!

18:41.078 --> 18:42.538
OHH!

18:42.621 --> 18:47.709
I AM VERY DISAPPOINTED
IN YOU BOYS.

18:47.793 --> 18:51.713
{\an1}WOW, SHE'S GOING TO NEED SOME
HEAVY-DUTY SOAP TO CLEAN HER UP.

18:53.507 --> 18:57.052
I'LL BE BACK IN 5 MINUTES.

18:57.135 --> 18:58.053
DON'T GIVE ME THAT LOOK.

18:58.136 --> 19:00.305
I WAS B-U-S-Y.

19:00.389 --> 19:01.473
DON'T SPELL AT ME.

19:01.557 --> 19:03.392
I HATE IT WHEN
YOU SPELL AT ME.

19:03.475 --> 19:05.894
{\an5}IT WAS YOUR TURN
TO WASH THE BABY.
SO WASH IT!

19:05.978 --> 19:07.896
{\an4}WHY DON'T YOU GET
YOUR NEW BEST BUDDY SETH
TO WASH THE BABY?

19:07.980 --> 19:10.816
{\an1}"OH, SETH,
PARTY AT MY HOUSE.

19:10.899 --> 19:12.693
{\an1}GREAT. LOVE YA.
BYE!"

19:12.776 --> 19:14.862
NEW TIP FOR THE GUIDE:

19:14.945 --> 19:17.197
WHO NEEDS YOU, ANYWAY?

19:17.281 --> 19:18.407
Kids: FIGHT! FIGHT!

19:18.490 --> 19:20.409
FIGHT! FIGHT!
FIGHT! FIGHT!

19:20.492 --> 19:21.618
{\an8}HELLO, EVERYBODY!

19:21.702 --> 19:24.788
{\an7}ALONG WITH MY PARTNER,
OLYMPIC GOLD MEDALLIST
WILLIE GAULT,

19:24.872 --> 19:26.123
{\an7}I'M VAN EARL WRIGHT
WELCOMING YOU TO

19:26.206 --> 19:28.917
{\an7}NED AND COOKIE'S
FIRST BIG FIGHT EVER.

19:29.001 --> 19:32.254
Kids: FIGHT! FIGHT!
FIGHT! FIGHT!

19:32.337 --> 19:34.339
{\an1}NEW TIP FOR YOUR
STUPID LITTLE GUIDE:

19:34.423 --> 19:37.259
BACK OFF, 'CAUSE I'M
A BAD MAN!

19:37.342 --> 19:42.139
{\an4}YOU MEAN YOU'RE
A DIGITAL DORK AND SO NOT
A CYBORG, EVER!

19:42.222 --> 19:44.266
Kids: OHH!

19:44.349 --> 19:45.475
{\an1}SO, WILLIE, WHO DO YOU
LIKE IN THIS FIGHT?

19:45.559 --> 19:48.020
NOBODY.

19:48.103 --> 19:50.939
{\an5}AND I'M NOT SURE IF
THESE GUYS COULD EVEN
BEAT UP A THIRD-GRADER.

19:51.023 --> 19:54.484
YOU DO NOT WANT
SOME OF THIS!

19:54.568 --> 19:58.447
{\an1}OH, YOU DO NOT WANT
ANY OF THIS!

19:58.530 --> 19:59.239
SOMEBODY HIT SOMEBODY!

20:04.202 --> 20:07.205
{\an4}WILLIE, WHAT KIND OF ADVICE
WOULD YOU GIVE TO
FRIENDS WHO FIGHT?

20:07.289 --> 20:10.626
{\an8}MY ADVICE IS
DON'T FIGHT.
TALK IT OUT.

20:10.709 --> 20:12.794
{\an8}BECAUSE THINGS COULD
GET UGLY QUICK,

20:12.878 --> 20:15.964
{\an8}AND THIS THING IS UGLY
IN ALL KIND OF WAYS.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.549
OH, I'M WAITING!

20:17.633 --> 20:20.469
{\an1}ME, TOO!

20:20.552 --> 20:21.470
Kids: US, TOO!

20:21.553 --> 20:22.471
[RECORD SCRATCH]

20:22.554 --> 20:25.057
[CRICKETS CHIRP]

20:25.140 --> 20:25.265
[BELL RINGS]

20:28.936 --> 20:29.978
King Bee: COOKIE!

20:30.062 --> 20:32.731
{\an4}WE'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOR YOU.
COME ON.

20:34.733 --> 20:36.693
{\an1}UH-OH. IT LOOKS LIKE
THE KILLER BEES

20:36.777 --> 20:38.153
{\an1}ARE HERE
TO BACK UP COOKIE.

20:38.236 --> 20:41.406
{\an1}I THINK THIS FIGHT THAT
NEVER REALLY WAS A FIGHT,

20:41.490 --> 20:43.951
{\an1}MORE LIKE A TOUGH POSE
CONTEST, IS OVER.

20:44.034 --> 20:45.994
WANNA HIT THE CAFETERIA?

20:46.078 --> 20:48.288
{\an5}LET'S DO IT.

20:46.078 --> 20:48.288
YOU'RE BUYING.

20:48.372 --> 20:52.668
EXCUSE ME WHILE
I BUZZ O-F-F.

20:54.920 --> 20:56.588
FINE.
LEAVE ME HERE WITH THE BABY

20:56.672 --> 20:58.590
{\an1}WHILE YOU GO HANG OUT
WITH YOUR FRIENDS!

21:03.804 --> 21:06.932
WE HAVE YOUR JACKET.

21:07.015 --> 21:09.393
{\an1}OH, BUT THERE'S ONE
LITTLE THING YOU HAVE TO DO

21:09.476 --> 21:12.729
{\an1}BEFORE YOU CAN BECOME
AN OFFICIAL KILLER BEE.

21:12.813 --> 21:13.855
WHAT?

21:13.939 --> 21:15.065
{\an5}YOU HAVE TO HACK
INTO THE SCHOOL'S
COMPUTER SYSTEM

21:15.148 --> 21:18.819
{\an5}AND CHANGE OUR
MATH GRADES
FROM Cs TO As.

21:18.902 --> 21:19.861
CHANGE YOUR MATH GRADES?

21:19.945 --> 21:22.072
NO WAY!
I'LL GET EXPELLED.

21:23.073 --> 21:25.534
NED WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU GUYS.

21:25.617 --> 21:27.077
{\an1}HEY, COOK.

21:27.160 --> 21:29.371
{\an1}WE TRIED BEING NICE
TO YOU,

21:29.454 --> 21:31.665
{\an1}AND WE TRIED GIVING YOU
THIS NICE JACKET.

21:31.748 --> 21:32.708
BUT NOW WE'RE TELLING YOU.

21:32.791 --> 21:34.710
NO. I WON'T.

21:34.793 --> 21:37.671
CHANGE OUR MATH GRADES,
OR YOU'RE GOING D-O-W-N.

21:38.797 --> 21:40.090
THE CYBORG SAID NO.

21:40.173 --> 21:42.551
{\an1}NED, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

21:42.634 --> 21:43.635
I DON'T KNOW.

21:43.719 --> 21:44.678
I SAW IT IN A MOVIE,

21:44.761 --> 21:47.723
{\an5}BUT NOW
IT SEEMS REALLY,
REALLY WRONG.

21:47.806 --> 21:48.932
{\an1}I'M SORRY.
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

21:49.016 --> 21:51.059
{\an1}I SHOULD'VE WASHED
THE BABY.

21:51.143 --> 21:53.145
NO, I'M SORRY.
I FELT LEFT OUT.

21:53.228 --> 21:54.146
YOU'RE TOTALLY COOL
AND TOUGH.

21:54.229 --> 21:57.065
{\an1}HEY! QUIT THE SWEET
BUDDY-BUDDY TALK

21:57.149 --> 21:58.567
{\an1}AND SAVE IT
FOR THE HOSPITAL.

21:58.650 --> 22:00.736
HEY! DO YOU KIDS
HAVE HALL PASSES?

22:00.819 --> 22:02.237
OK, GREAT.

22:02.320 --> 22:05.949
{\an1}NOW IT'S TIME TO KICK
SOME B-U-T-T.

22:06.033 --> 22:09.411
BACK OFF, OR I'LL
MAKE YOU BACK OFF.

22:09.494 --> 22:11.079
Both: AAH!

22:11.163 --> 22:12.789
King Bee: OH, YEAH,
MOSLEY?

22:12.873 --> 22:13.957
YOU AND WHAT ARMY?

22:18.045 --> 22:19.379
OH, RIGHT,
THAT ARMY.

22:21.798 --> 22:22.716
[BELL RINGS]

22:22.799 --> 22:24.426
HA HA HA!

22:27.471 --> 22:29.014
{\an1}YOU NEVER REALLY KNOW
WHO YOUR TRUE FRIENDS ARE

22:29.097 --> 22:31.266
{\an1}UNTIL YOUR BACK'S
TO THE WALL.

22:31.349 --> 22:32.225
{\an1}SHE HELPED ME SAVE
YOU GUYS' BUTTS,

22:32.309 --> 22:35.270
BUT I HAVE NOTHING IN COMMON
WITH DORIS.

22:35.353 --> 22:38.398
{\an1}I HAVE NO IDEA HOW SHE ACED
MY FAKE YEARBOOK SURVEY.

22:38.482 --> 22:40.150
Doris: SURVEY?

22:40.233 --> 22:42.027
{\an1}THAT WASN'T A STUDY HALL QUIZ
I CHEATED ON?

22:42.110 --> 22:43.779
CHEATED ON?

22:43.862 --> 22:46.198
{\an1}YEAH. I COPIED ALL
THE ANSWERS FROM CRABGRASS.

22:46.281 --> 22:47.741
CRABGRASS?!

22:47.824 --> 22:50.869
{\an5}SUZIE CRABGRASS
SCORED 100% ON MY
BEST FRIEND QUIZ?!

22:56.416 --> 22:58.960
SHE'S REALLY
SCARED OF US.

22:59.044 --> 23:01.630
THAT'S IT.
I'M OUT. SORRY.

23:01.713 --> 23:02.464
FINE.

23:02.547 --> 23:04.883
{\an1}YOU'RE ALL WRONG
FOR THE CREW, ANYWAY.

23:04.966 --> 23:08.303
{\an1}TO WEAR THIS JACKET,
YOU HAVE TO LOVE BEING TOUGH

23:08.386 --> 23:11.348
AND LOVE TALKING ABOUT NED.

23:13.225 --> 23:14.476
[GIRLS LAUGH]

23:14.559 --> 23:16.478
SO THEN WHAT DID NED DO?

23:16.561 --> 23:19.564
THEN NED RAN INTO THE GIRLS'
ROOM...ACCIDENTALLY!

23:19.648 --> 23:21.942
{\an8}Ned: SO, IF YOU HIT
A BEST FRIEND ROUGH SPOT,

23:22.025 --> 23:24.194
{\an8}TALK IT OUT, 'CAUSE ANYTHING IS
BETTER THAN FIGHTING.

23:24.277 --> 23:26.196
{\an8}SO THINGS WITH YOU
AND COOKIE ARE COOL?

23:26.279 --> 23:27.114
{\an7}OH, YEAH.

23:27.197 --> 23:28.156
{\an1}HE GOT A NICE JACKET
EVEN THOUGH

23:28.240 --> 23:29.491
HE DIDN'T JOIN THE BEES.

23:29.574 --> 23:30.534
SO WHAT ARE YOU
DOING TONIGHT?

23:30.617 --> 23:30.909
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

23:30.992 --> 23:32.828
HEY, NED.

23:32.911 --> 23:34.788
{\an1}I'M PSYCHED FOR
YOUR PARTY TONIGHT.

23:34.871 --> 23:38.041
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND,
BUT I INVITED A FEW FRIENDS.

23:38.125 --> 23:39.084
All: SEE YOU TONIGHT, NED!

23:39.167 --> 23:40.919
{\an1}I THINK
I'M HAVING A PARTY.

